data: {"type":"response.output_item.done","item":{"type":"a2a_preview_call_output","id":"fco_08d44d12d6348e99006a15da2b71a08193bfa9c34bae05cc8c","agent_reference":{"type":"agent_reference","name":"cs-e2e-tests-client","version":"1"},"response_id":"resp_08d44d12d6348e99006a15da0b041081938ca6cd27f6b85e2f","call_id":"call_fded7e862ecd42c2b16ab229ceb34ecb","name":"workiqc4k5h8","output":"I found **3 meetings scheduled on your calendar for today**. Here’s a clear breakdown to help you plan the rest of your day:\n\n---\n\n## \uD83D\uDCC5 Today’s Meetings\n\n### 1. [DevEx Engineering: weekly meeting](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAIOdCAHwAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=e3ab957a-2458-441f-9127-05e70141eaf4) 【1-c6191b】\n- **Time:** 4:05 PM – 5:00 PM  \n- **Organizer:** [Travis Wilson](https://www.office.com/search?q=Travis+Wilson&EntityRepresentationId=1e09982a-1dbe-4f55-97b9-09b2c83b3577) 【1-c6191b】  \n- **Location:** Microsoft Teams + Conf Rooms (Building 16) 【1-c6191b】  \n- **Status:** ✅ Already occurred  \n\n---\n\n### 2. [AI Foundry SDK/API Reviews](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QADjeEUBgAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=123a2562-ad87-4cf1-a036-26647f149e2e) 【2-fa350d】\n- **Time:** 6:05 PM – 7:00 PM  \n- **Organizer:** [Dan Taylor](https://www.office.com/search?q=Dan+Taylor&EntityRepresentationId=ac6e9d0e-97e6-4ff8-93d9-ecb05c2f7097) 【2-fa350d】  \n- **Location:** Microsoft Teams  \n- **Your Response:** Tentatively accepted  \n- **Note:** ⚠️ Conflicts with [Team Lunch](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QADjeFGvwAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=f54420a5-63e3-42e8-b638-b531646a2c20) 【2-fa350d】  \n\n---\n\n### 3. [Team Lunch](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QADjeFGvwAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=f54420a5-63e3-42e8-b638-b531646a2c20) 【3-bb70e1】\n- **Time:** 6:45 PM – 8:00 PM  \n- **Organizer:** [Travis Angevine](https://www.office.com/search?q=Travis+Angevine&EntityRepresentationId=ce195fbc-d351-4a94-8aa9-3d293b249413) 【3-bb70e1】  \n- **Location:** Building 16 Lobby  \n- **Note:** ⚠️ Overlaps with [AI Foundry SDK/API Reviews](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QADjeEUBgAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=123a2562-ad87-4cf1-a036-26647f149e2e) 【3-bb70e1】  \n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ Conflict to be aware of\n- [AI Foundry SDK/API Reviews](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QADjeEUBgAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=123a2562-ad87-4cf1-a036-26647f149e2e) and [Team Lunch](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meeting/details?eventId=AAMkAGI4NTJlOTY2LWVhYTgtNDUwMy04MmFlLTBiOTFhY2EyYmI5NAFRAAgI3rq5ut3AAEYAAAAAxlcDfIcKC0iM2tlcAvavNgcAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QAAAAABDQAAUK8J1_iHKU2PtUBJgHeK-QADjeFGvwAAEA%3d%3d&EntityRepresentationId=f54420a5-63e3-42e8-b638-b531646a2c20) overlap between **6:45 PM – 7:00 PM**, so you’ll need to choose or split time between them.\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Quick Suggestions\n- Since you’ve **tentatively accepted** the SDK/API review, you might want to:\n  - Join the review briefly for key updates, then head to lunch, or  \n  - Follow the meeting instead if lunch is more important for team bonding\n\n---\n\nIf you want, I can help you **resolve the conflict** (e.g., accept one, decline or follow the other) or pull **agenda/notes** for either meeting so you can decide quickly.\n","status":"completed"},"output_index":1,"sequence_number":6}

